image.altText: A photo of Gymnastics coach Jeb Silsbury. He is smiling in the photo

props.synopsis: An Australian gymnastics coach selected for the Paris Olympics is accused of making comments about a former colleague's breasts and calling her a "minion".

title.children: Gymnastics coach withdraws from Olympics after allegations of inappropriate behaviour raised

image.altText: Aerial shot of massive oil and gas rig in the Bass Strait off Victoria

props.synopsis: Offshore gas supplies are running out in the Bass Strait and there are plans to dismantle some of Esso's ocean gas rigs. But the company's intention to leave parts of them in the sea has sparked concerns.

title.children: Mercury and asbestos are in decommissioned Bass Strait gas rigs. A fight is brewing over their removal

image.altText: Shelley Duvall with short blonde hair and a fringe smiles at the camera wearing a red shirt

props.synopsis: Shelley Duvall — a regular star in some of the defining movies of the 1970s and 1980s — dies decades after retreating from the spotlight and settling in a small town in Texas.

title.children: Shelley Duvall — star of The Shining and a regular in Robert Altman films — dies aged 75

image.altText: The court logo on the Melbourne Magistrates' Court.

props.synopsis: Michael Stanyer breached consumer law and called debtors "dickheads" and "pathetic lying losers", then told a magistrate he won't be paying his fine.

title.children: Debt collector who refuses to pay fine faces five-year ban over harassing calls

image.altText: Woman wearing an Akubra hat in selfie

props.synopsis: Call for the mandatory return of income support management has some on the edge of tears and fears people could leave towns to avoid the reintroduction.

title.children: 'Don't think we'd survive it': Anxieties that Morrison-era policy could return amid cost-of-living crisis

image.altText: Jen Daine stands under two bridges and looks up into the distrance.

props.synopsis: Commercial photographer Jen Dainer was applying for the Army Reserve when a question about the date of her last period stopped her in her tracks. A Department of Defence spokesperson said the content of the questionnaire is being revised.

title.children: 'Like asking a man what his sperm count is': Should the ADF ask applicants about their periods?

image.altText: A drawing of a mammoth surrounded by tusks and bones

props.synopsis: An incredibly well-preserved woolly mammoth specimen that died 52,000 years ago in Siberia has now had its chromosome structure reassembled for the first time.

title.children: First ancient chromosomes reconstructed from 52,000-year-old woolly mammoth

image.altText: An Aboriginal woman gazes into the distance

props.synopsis: A prominent anti-violence campaigner has called on the Northern Territory government to involve community elders in discussions about strategies to quell violent unrest beyond the snap curfew.

title.children: Anti-violence campaigner says government must listen to 'voices from the bush' after Alice Springs curfew

image.altText: A woman stands in front of a wall in Kyiv. Behind the wall there appears to be a timber baricade

props.synopsis: Yulia was filming on her phone in Kyiv when a nearby children's hospital was struck by a Russian missile. She says it "literally looked like Armageddon".

title.children: 'Like Armageddon': Kyiv resident recalls moment children's hospital was hit

image.altText: Joe Biden speaks at a podium with two microphones and points straight ahead. A door and flag are behind him.

props.synopsis: Fist fights broke out the last time the Democratic Party's presidential candidate was decided on the convention floor in 1968.

image.altText: An older man in a suit with a bright red cap gestures as he speaks behind a lectern.

props.synopsis: The implications for what happens next in the race for the White House have ramifications that stretch far beyond US shores. And that's a key reason why Australia and China are closely watching what happens next.

title.children: Trump says he could end the Russia-Ukraine war 'within a day'. It's enough to send shivers down Australia's spine

image.altText: A man and woman smiling

title.children: 'It's just a way of life': Greyhound trainers in NSW insist the industry has improved despite damning report from former head vet

image.altText: Richard Marles and Joe Biden shake hands.

props.synopsis: The Australian government is set to give Ukraine another $250 million in military support — its largest contribution to the war effort to date.

title.children: Australia pledges biggest ever boost for Ukraine as NATO calls out China as Russia's 'enabler'

image.altText: A picture of St Kilda AFL coach Ross Lyon standing on the sidelines at Docklands looking out on the field during a match.

props.synopsis: St Kilda coach Ross Lyon hopes last week's upset win over ladder leaders Sydney can help kick-start the Saints' development in his second stint in charge.

title.children: St Kilda coach hopes upset can spark a Saints revival

image.altText: Ed John. Executive Manager, Stewardship at the Melbourne office in July 2022.

props.synopsis: CEO bonuses are becoming a "given" according to a long-running study, despite a rise in investor strikes against remuneration reports.

title.children: Corporate governance experts urge moderation in CEO bonus pay

image.altText: A man in handcuffs is escorted through a doorway by two policemen, with one holding him by the arm

image.altText: A Sydney Swans AFL player stands next to a St Kilda opponent who is being helped by a trainer, and speaks to the other player.

image.altText: A group of people gather

image.altText: Two police officers in tactical gear stand on a street with their backs to the camera

image.altText: The outside of a hotel

image.altText: A cathedral with black smoke

props.synopsis: The cathedral is widely known as it was painted several times by French impressionist painter Claude Monet in the 19th century.

title.children: Ancient French cathedral made famous by Monet catches fire

image.altText: A close up of Joe Biden speaking passionately and pointing with his right hand

props.synopsis: US President Joe Biden is facing fresh doubts about his re-election chances from heavyweights Nancy Pelosi and George Clooney, and analysts say it's likely he'll give into the pressure.

title.children: 'He'll keep digging his heels in until he doesn't': Pressure mounts on Biden to step aside

image.altText: Former West Coast Eagles defender Brad Sheppard standing outside of the Broome Toyota showroom.

props.synopsis: Retired footballer Brad Sheppard is suing his former club, the West Coast Eagles, the AFL as well as two doctors over claims of 'medical negligence.'

image.altText: Black plumes of smoke rise from a factory fire in suburban Melbourne.

title.children: Melbourne factory gutted by explosive blaze was recently put on notice by watchdog

image.altText: A grass strip next to a road with multiple bouquets of flowers and a wooden cross.

props.synopsis: ACT Policing confirms there were two other people in the stolen Toyota Camry when it hit a concrete barrier and flipped near Parliament House in April this year, leaving a 15-year-old dead.

image.altText: A woman in a light green jacket talks to police officers in dark jackets outside with trees in background.

props.synopsis: Aboriginal leaders in Geraldton are calling for cultural change within WA Police following a week of coronial hearings into the fatal shooting of a First Nations woman in the Midwest.

title.children: 'No empathy': Indigenous leaders seek greater cultural understanding from police amid fatal shooting inquest

image.altText: NATO

props.synopsis: The newly elected UK prime minister shares the international podium with his European partners and meets with Joe Biden in the White House after promising to continue backing Ukraine in its fight against Russia.

image.altText: Side portrait of woman with pink and purple hair, wearing a leopard print top.

image.altText: An embossed metal sign on a building that reads "Department of Education".

image.altText: Catholic Archbishop of Perth Timothy Costelloe arrives for the parliamentary inquiry hearing.

image.altText: Aerial image of the tug pens and bulk carriers at a port

image.altText: A pink, furless joey the size of a jellybean can be seen as a gloved hand checks inside the pouch of a wallaby

image.altText: Two unidentified people wearing jackets with "Australian Federal Police" and "Forensics" on the back.

props.synopsis: A man released by the High Court following the NZYQ decision has been charged with breaching his visa conditions by visiting within 200 metres of a school or childcare centre on eight separate occasions.

image.altText: Suburban street scene from above

props.synopsis: The words "gutless" and "heartless" have been painted on to the windows of Jacinta Allan's office in Central Victoria overnight.
